// Adversarial: Three SpeedBoost effects registered on distinct bump-timing triggers —
// EarlyBumped (0.85x, a slight penalty), PerfectBumped (1.3x), LateBumped (0.9x, mild
// penalty). Dense layout and chaos 0.5 drive a mix of all three timing outcomes.
// The adversarial risk: if the trigger bridge incorrectly fires multiple timing variants
// for the same bump event, stacked multipliers compound and blow past BoltMaxSpeed.
// If timing tags are never cleared between bumps, old multipliers accumulate silently.
// BoltSpeedAccurate is the primary detector — it fires the moment bolt speed leaves the
// configured min/max envelope. 5000 frames at moderate chaos ensures enough bump events
// to exercise the full timing spectrum including back-to-back mixed timings.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.5)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltSpeedAccurate],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 6174,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: Bolt, then: [
            When(trigger: EarlyBumped, then: [
                Do(SpeedBoost(multiplier: 0.85)),
            ]),
            When(trigger: PerfectBumped, then: [
                Do(SpeedBoost(multiplier: 1.3)),
            ]),
            When(trigger: LateBumped, then: [
                Do(SpeedBoost(multiplier: 0.9)),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
